ðŸ§© What is Encapsulation?

Definition (Simple):
Encapsulation means wrapping the data (variables) and methods (functions) that operate on the data together in a single unit (class) and restricting direct 
access to some of the classâ€™s components.
It helps protect the data from being changed directly.

We access data using getter and setter methods.

ðŸ§  Key Points:
Use private for variables â†’ cannot access them directly from outside the class.

Use public getter and setter methods â†’ to read or modify private variables safely.

Helps in data hiding and controlling how data is accessed or modified.


****/// code example  ///*****


// Encapsulation Example
class Student {
    // Private variables (cannot be accessed directly)
    private String name;
    private int age;

    // Setter methods (to set values)
    public void setName(String n) {
        name = n;
    }

    public void setAge(int a) {
        if(a > 0) { // validation
            age = a;
        }
    }

    // Getter methods (to get values)
    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }

    public int getAge() {
        return age;
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s = new Student();

        // Using setter to set values
        s.setName("Rahul");
        s.setAge(20);

        // Using getter to get values
        System.out.println("Name: " + s.getName());
        System.out.println("Age: " + s.getAge());
    }
}
